prerequisites.description:
Add 4 new ExprKind variants to crates/reify-syntax/src/lib.rs (after existing variants, before Auto):

```rust
/// List literal: `[1, 2, 3]`
ListLiteral(Vec<Expr>),
/// Set literal: `set{1, 2, 3}`
SetLiteral(Vec<Expr>),
/// Map literal: `map{"a" => 1, "b" => 2}`
MapLiteral(Vec<(Expr, Expr)>),
/// Index access: `expr[index]`
IndexAccess {
    object: Box<Expr>,
    index: Box<Expr>,
},
```

These are type-only changes with no logic.

Add placeholder match arms in crates/reify-compiler/src/lib.rs compile_expr() for the 4 new ExprKind variants. Each emits a diagnostic and returns Undef, following the existing MemberAccess pattern:

```rust
reify_syntax::ExprKind::ListLiteral(_) => {
    diagnostics.push(Diagnostic::error("list literals not yet supported in compiler").with_label(DiagnosticLabel::new(expr.span, "unsupported")));
    CompiledExpr::literal(Value::Undef, Type::Real)
}
```

Same pattern for SetLiteral, MapLiteral, IndexAccess. This keeps the exhaustive match and prevents compilation failure.
